      "message": "Not necessarily to address in this change, but mentioning as I looked at screenshot:\n- it isn\u0027t immediately apparent whether it\u0027s 0, 1, 2, ... out of the total number of filtered results, or out of the total results in the run, period.\n- presuming it\u0027s probably filtered, there\u0027s no way to see how many total filtered results there are currently\n\nSo when you\u0027re looking at it, you see like index #3 but you don\u0027t know if it\u0027s out of 8,000 or 300 that meet the filtering criteria, and that is material info.\n\nVarious ways to address such as putting / \u003ctotal\u003e alongside each result index (but that\u0027s sort of verbose), or having a total in one place at top of page, or having the total on a separate details page.",
